<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="440" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1043,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1043,1069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Thorax black, except pronotum, proepisternum, posterior margin of anepisternum, almost all the katepisternum, laterotergite and rectangular macule on notopleuron yellow to whitish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1210,1079,1105]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1224,1240,1080,1106]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">7</figureCitation>
). Femora yellow, except apical half of fore femur and two dorsal dark irregular spots on mid and hind femora (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1247,1115,1141]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1260,1276,1115,1141]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">8</figureCitation>
). Wing: costal vein with a bilobed finger-shaped projection on basal third; r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[834,842,1170,1184]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">1</subScript>
with longitudinal macula underlying costal vein; r 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1411,1437,1169,1183]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">4+5</subScript>
closed near wing apex, forming a petiole (
<figureCitation box="[622,725,1187,1213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Figs 2–3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="442" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1043,2042]" box="[199,1050,1222,1250]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,413,1223,1249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[428,493,1223,1249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length [
<typeStatus box="[669,777,1222,1249]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">holotype</typeStatus>
]: 
<quantity box="[793,882,1223,1250]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" unit="mm" value="7.6">7.6 mm</quantity>
; wing 
<quantity box="[957,1046,1223,1250]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="440" unit="mm" value="5.3">5.3 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1043,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,1259,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Head.</emphasis>
Dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[434,505,1259,1285]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
): mesofrons black, distinctly striated, strongly excavated on frontal vitta; anterior part of mesofrons and parafrons orangish yellow, parafrons covered with dense silvery pruinosity; epicephalon and ocellar tubercle shinning black and covered by weak silvery pruinosity. Frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1199,1331,1358]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): parafacial and face orangish yellow, parafacial with several pale setulae, covered with dense silvery pruinosity. Lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1352,1422,1367,1394]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
): gena and postgena orangish yellow, with short sparse black setae, and covered by weak silvery pruinosity; occiput black; mouthparts brownish. Antenna orangish brown, pedicel with crown of setae, one longer than postpedicel length on ventral margin, arista brown, short pubescent on basal fourth; inner and outer-vertical bristles, and postocellar bristles black, well developed and subequal in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1043,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,1547,1573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[303,371,1547,1574]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Black, except pronotum, proepisternum, posterior margin of anepisternum, almost all the katepisternum, laterotergite and rectangular macule on notopleuron yellow to whitish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1251,1583,1609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1277,1414,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Chaetotaxy:</emphasis>
1 notopleural, 1 supra-alar, 1 postalar, 2 scutellar apical and 1 katepisternal bristles all long and black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1043,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,1655,1681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[269,339,1655,1681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[352,368,1655,1681]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">8</figureCitation>
). Fore leg dark brown, except apical half of coxa, trochanter and basal half of femur yellow; mid leg yellow, except two dorsal irregular spots on femur (one at mid-length and one pre-apical) and apex, apex of tibia and tarsus dark brown; hind leg yellow, except two dorsal irregular spots on apical half of femur and apex, apex of tibia and tarsus dark brown. 
<emphasis box="[471,607,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Chaetotaxy:</emphasis>
fore tibia with 2 short dorsal setae at basal 1/3; mid femur with antero- to posteroventral long and fine setae at basal 3/4, antero- and posteroventral rows of spiniform setae on apical half (
<figureCitation box="[160,227,1835,1861]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1136,1160]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[151,1435,201,1113]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 4–6. Head; 4. Dorsal view; 5. Frontal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Thorax, dorsal view; 8. Mid femur, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306176/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); mid tibia with dorsal and posterodorsal rows of short setae; hind tibia with two dorsal rows of short setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1043,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,264,1871,1897]" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[281,385,1871,1897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Figs 2–3</figureCitation>
). Membrane hyaline, veins pale brown: costal vein densely setose, ending at petiole formed by the veins R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[317,343,1925,1939]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[422,430,1926,1940]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">1</subScript>
; costal vein with a bilobed finger-shaped projection on basal third, each lobe with short spiniform setae (
<figureCitation box="[342,411,1943,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="440">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
