<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1242,1989]" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1242,1268]" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[330,395,1243,1269]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@2.[160,1427,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., holotype ³. 1. Lateral habitus; 2. Wing, dorsal view; 3. Finger-shaped projection on costal vein.Abbreviations: C = costal vein; M1 = first branch of media; M4 = fourth branch of media; R2+3= second branch of radius; R4+5 = third branch of radius." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306174" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306174/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Tergites dark brown, except proximal portion of syntergite 1+2 and distal portion of tergites 3–6 and all tergite 7 pale, covered with short black setae; sternites dark brown with lateral margins pale yellow, and covered with long pale setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[486,617,1314,1340]" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[632,750,1315,1341]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,190,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., paratype ³. 9. Abdomen and terminalia, lateral view; 10. Left surstylus, lateral view; 11. Right surstylus, lateral view; 12. Claspers, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306178" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306178/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
). Sternite 5 with one pair of claspers, with setose margin and strong black bristles at apex, each clasper with a finger-shaped short projection next to the base (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1349,1351,1377]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,190,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., paratype ³. 9. Abdomen and terminalia, lateral view; 10. Left surstylus, lateral view; 11. Right surstylus, lateral view; 12. Claspers, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306178" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306178/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Figs 9, 12</figureCitation>
). Epandrial capsule black dorsally, pale laterally and ventrally, covered with long pale setae. Left surstylus pale with dark apex, wide, with two projections, one anterior long with rounded apex and one apical short with pointed apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,190,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., paratype ³. 9. Abdomen and terminalia, lateral view; 10. Left surstylus, lateral view; 11. Right surstylus, lateral view; 12. Claspers, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306178" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306178/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Right surstylus U-shaped, pale, except apex of posterior branch dark; anterior branch with bifid apex and one short pre-apical protuberance, posterior branch slightly longer than anterior and apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1216,1298,1495,1521]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,190,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Micropeza chiroptera sp. nov., paratype ³. 9. Abdomen and terminalia, lateral view; 10. Left surstylus, lateral view; 11. Right surstylus, lateral view; 12. Claspers, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306178" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4306178/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1242,1989]" box="[199,418,1531,1557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1531,1557]" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1242,1989]" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1566,1592]" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">Variation.</emphasis>
Mid and hind femora with only a slightly pre-apical infuscation; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1085,1093,1585,1599]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="442">4</subScript>
present only as a weak fold in the wing.
</paragraph>
